hopobject.body: No, I'm not particularly sporty tinytoeshealthyglows.co.uk China's shadow banking boomed after a 2010 directive from Chinese authorities to restrict the flow of bank loans. Beijing was worried that the waves of loans prompted from a 2008 stimulus package was pushing up inflation, among other concerns. Banks could lend to state-backed companies, but most of China's other corporations would have to find other methods of accessing capital.
